quran[9]{c,v,t,f}:
  23,88,"Say "
  23,89,"They will say: "
  23,90,"Nay, but We have brought them the truth (Islâmic Monotheism), and verily, they (disbelievers) are liars."
  25,34,"Those who will be gathered to Hell (prone) on their faces, such will be in an evil state, and most astray from the (Straight) Path.{1}",footnotes:1:{25:34} See the footnote of (Verse 17:97).
  25,35,"And indeed We gave Mûsâ (Moses) the Scripture [the Taurât (Torah)], and placed his brother Hârûn (Aaron) with him as a helper;"
  25,36,"And We said: "
  26,7,"Do they not observe the earth - how much of every good kind We cause to grow therein?"
  26,8,"Verily, in this is an Ayâh (proof or sign), yet most of them (polytheists, pagans who do not believe in Resurrection) are not believers."
  26,9,"And verily your Lord, He is truly the All-Mighty, the Most Merciful."